# The reader disambiguates a contextual keyword purely by grammatical position (spec/grammar.md:230,
# 365): the SAME word `empty` is an ordinary place/variable when it follows `:`, and the predicate
# keyword when it immediately follows `is`. Likewise `member` names a variable AND heads the
# `is member of` predicate. Both roles coexist in one program with no parse diagnostic.
:empty = [1 2 3]
print :empty is empty
:member = [4 5 6]
print 5 is member of :member
